div1.p:
Q.(to
John Wood
) Which are the bags you marked. - A. These two bags were marked by me, they are my master's property, I believe the other bags to be my master's property, but I should not like to swear to them.

Q. Did you see the prisoner there. - A. No, I found him at No. 16, Tottenham Court Road. When he came to the door to me, he says, master, I hope if I let you have the things again, you will not do any thing to me; 
               Warren
             the constable was with me, I told him he was the man, he told him he had a warrant against him, he must go with him; the prisoner went with us to the Berwick Arms, in Castle-street, and the tools were brought up out of the cellar, the prisoner took them on his back, and carried them to the office in Marlborough-street.
